Markets appear confident that the Omicron variant is not as bad as initially feared. AFP/Justin Tallis JOHANNESBURG - Professor Tulio de Oliveira from UKZN's Krisp institute says the omicron variant is much milder when it comes to deaths and hospitalisation. The COVID-19 infection rate has been on a steady decline in the country. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 5,920 new cases recorded On Thursday, 5,920 new infections were recorded, with the positivity rate standing at 14.3-percent. Meanwhile, some experts believe South Africa may be ready to transition from treating COVID-19 as a pandemic to endemic disease. But the Health Department is still debating this.